getSupportingTerms

List<KAMStoreDaoImpl.BelTerm> getSupportingTerms(Kam.KamNode node,
                                                 boolean removeDups,
                                                 KAMCatalogDao.NamespaceFilter fltr)
                                                 throws KamStoreException
Returns a list of BEL term objects which support the KAM node. If removeDuplicates is true, the list of terms returned is reduced to the list of unique terms based on namespace identifiers. If namespaceFilter is set, the list of terms reported is initially filtered with respect to the filter criteria.

Parameters:
node - KAM node
fltr - Namespace filter
removeDups - Flag to control removal of duplicate terms
Returns:
List of BEL terms
Throws:
KamStoreException - Thrown if the list of BEL terms could not be retrieved

getKamNodes

List<Kam.KamNode> getKamNodes(Kam k,
                              FunctionEnum function,
                              KAMStoreDaoImpl.Namespace ns,
                              String paramValue)
                              throws KamStoreException
Find all KAM nodes that match the given function and that were compiled with the given namespace, and parameter value.
This method will not return nodes that were compiled with equivalents of the given namespace and parameter value. Use getKamNodes(Kam, FunctionEnum, SkinnyUUID) to search all equivalents.

Parameters:
k - KAM
function - FunctionEnum
ns - KAMStoreDaoImpl.Namespace
paramValue - Parameter value
Returns:
List of KAM node
Throws:
KamStoreException - Throw if an error occurred while retrieving the KAM nodes

getKamNodes

List<Kam.KamNode> getKamNodes(Kam k,
                              FunctionEnum function,
                              SkinnyUUID uuid)
                              throws KamStoreException
Find all Kam.KamNodes in the Kam that contain parameters identified by the given SkinnyUUIDs. This method finds nodes where the parameter occurs at any position. All functions will be returned.

Parameters:
uuid - SkinnyUUID identifying the parameter
k - kam
function - function
{@link - SkinnyUUID uuid} identifying the parameter
Returns:
Set of Kam.KamNodes containing the parameter identified by the SkinnyUUID. Note this identifier is namespace-agnostic; KamNodes that use any equivalent of the given UUID will be returned.
Throws:
KamStoreException - Thrown if an error occurred while retrieving the KAM nodes

getKamNodes

List<Kam.KamNode> getKamNodes(Kam k,
                              Kam.KamNode node)
                              throws KamStoreException
Find all KAM nodes that share node parameters with the example KAM node.

For instance, given a kam with the following nodes:

  • complex(p(1), g(2))
  • p(1)
  • g(2)
  • r(2)
  • act(r(2))
Providing the complex(p(1), g(2)) KAM node will yield the following KAM nodes:
  • p(1)
  • g(2)
  • r(2)
  • act(r(2))

Parameters:
k - KAM, the KAM that the nodes are contained within
node - Example KAM node, the KAM node to match on
Returns:
All KAM nodes that share node parameters with node
Throws:
KamStoreException - Thrown if an error occurred retrieving node candidates
